## ğŸ“‹ Usage Examples

### Run Once (Test)
```powershell
.\Zurg-Broken-Torrent-Monitor.ps1 -RunOnce
```

### Continuous Monitoring
```powershell
.\Zurg-Broken-Torrent-Monitor.ps1 -CheckIntervalMinutes 30
```

### With Custom URL
```powershell
.\Zurg-Broken-Torrent-Monitor.ps1 `
  -ZurgUrl "http://192.168.1.100:9999" `
  -Username "admin" `
  -Password "secret123"
```

---

## ğŸ› Troubleshooting

### "TotalTorrents shows 0"
- Check Zurg `/manage/` endpoint is accessible
- Verify authentication credentials
- Check logs with `-VerboseLogging`

### "Percentages don't add to 100%"
- Normal! Some torrents might be in other states
- Unrepairable, pending, etc. are not counted

### "Slow performance"
- Expected with 10,000+ torrents
- Consider increasing check interval
- Each check takes ~3-5 seconds max

